# Cursor Rules for NextBoi Project

Please follow these strict guidelines when writing code for this project.

## Tech Stack & Core Tools
- **Runtime & Manager**: Bun (use `bun run` for scripts, `bun test` for tests)
- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router)
- **React version**: React 19 (Canary/Stable)
- **Compiler**: React Compiler (automatic memoization, do not write manual useMemo/useCallback unless necessary)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS-first config inside globals.css)
- **Components**: shadcn/ui and @base-ui/react primitives
- **Linting & Formatting**: Biome (ensure `bun run check` has zero warnings)

## Code Standards & TypeScript
- Use strict TypeScript. Avoid `any`. Type all parameters and function return values explicitly.
- Declare explicit interfaces for states, components, and API responses.
- Implement server-client boundaries correctly. Default to Server Components. Use Client Components strictly at leaf components.
- Use modular structure under `src/features/[feature_name]/` for feature-specific hooks, services, and components.
- **Logic & UI Separation**: Extract all form state, mutations, and complex hooks into a dedicated custom logic hook (e.g. `use[Component]Logic`), leaving visual TSX files representational.
- **DOM Node Efficiency**: Minimize tag nesting. Avoid redundant wrapper `div` layers; use CSS flex, grid gap spacing, or semantic HTML tags directly.

## Tailwind CSS v4 & Styling Guidelines
- Config variables are inside `@theme inline` in `src/app/globals.css`.
- Rely on oklch format color palettes.
- Apply preset design utility classes:
  - `glass-panel` - frosted container backgrounds.
  - `glass-card` - frosted container backgrounds with smooth hover scaling/border highlights.
  - `bg-grid-mesh` - mesh background grids.

## Biome Formatting & Verification
- Prioritize running `bun run check` after changing files.
- Ensure all imports are sorted automatically by Biome.
- Group imports: React first, libraries second, local components third, styles last.

## Playwright E2E Testing
- All E2E test files reside under `./tests/` and use the `.spec.ts` suffix.
- Prioritize running `bun run test:e2e` to verify E2E journeys.
- Avoid locating text elements strictly if they appear multiple times; scope locators to parent containers.

## Card Spacings & Border styling
- Never mix outline rings (`ring-*`) and borders (`border-*`) on the same container (prevents overlapping concentric curves at rounded corners).
- Keep card containers clean, delegating spacing/paddings to children components using standard padding (`p-6`).
